<subSubSection pageId="370" pageNumber="371" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="370" pageNumber="371">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="370" pageNumber="371">
The range of this species extends from the Ontario Peninsula (Bousquet 1987a: 120) to southern British Columbia, north to western Alaska (Lindroth 1963b: 337-338), south to northern Oregon (Gilliam and Morrow Counties, CMNH; Hatch 1953: 90; Lindroth 1963b: 337), southern Arizona (Dajoz 2007: 21), western Texas (Jeff Davis County, MCZ), and northwestern Pennsylvania (Warren and Forest Counties, CMNH). The species has been reported also from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Mexico”">&quot;Mexico&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Casey 1924: 35, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1924" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="370" pageNumber="371" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aversans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="370" pageNumber="371">Bembidion aversans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The record from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“California”">&quot;California&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Bousquet and Larochelle 1993: 138) was based on a misidentified specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gebler" authorityYear="1833" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="370" pageNumber="371" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petrosum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="370" pageNumber="371">Bembidion petrosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in MCZ.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
